"title": "2595: incarnation",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "2595: incarnation",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The assuming by God of human nature in the person of Jesus Christ. The incarnation is the fixed and permanent physical dwelling of God in his world, as opposed to the temporary manifestation of the divine presence and power in a theophany.</p>\n<h2>God the Son assumed human nature</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:14\">JHN 1:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:9\">JHN 1:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:56\">JHN 8:56</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim3:16\">1TI 3:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John1:1-1John1:2\">1JN 1:1–1:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John4:2\">1JN 4:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2John1:7\">2JN 1:7</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ's incarnation involved a supernatural conception</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:35\">LUK 1:35</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa9:6\">ISA 9:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt1:18\">MAT 1:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:9\">JHN 14:9</a> <em>The incarnation was such that the Son was the exact representation of the Father</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:4\">ROM 1:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:15\">COL 1:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:19\">COL 1:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb1:2-Heb1:3\">HEB 1:2–1:3</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ Chist's incarnation involved a virgin birth</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt1:22-Matt1:23\">MAT 1:22–1:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa7:14\">ISA 7:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:34\">LUK 1:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:3\">ROM 1:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:4\">GAL 4:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:8\">PHP 2:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:14\">HEB 2:14</a></p>\n<h2>The cost of the incarnation</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:6-Phil2:7\">PHP 2:6–2:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor8:9\">2CO 8:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:10\">HEB 2:10</a> <em>The incarnation involved Jesus Christ's suffering.</em></p>\n<h2>The necessity of the incarnation</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:3\">ROM 8:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:17-Rom5:19\">ROM 5:17–5:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:19\">2CO 5:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:22\">COL 1:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim2:5\">1TI 2:5</a> <em>Only a person who is fully human and fully divine can be the effective mediator between God and humanity</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:17-Heb2:18\">HEB 2:17–2:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:15\">HEB 4:15</a></p>",
